When Viola made her second visit to Olivia , she found no difficulty in gaining access to her . 
No sooner had Viola left the lady than a claim was made upon her velour . 
A gentleman , a rejected suitor of Olivia , who had learned how that lady had favoured the duke's messenger , challenged him to fight a duel . 
You stand amazed , but be of comfort . 
And now the stranger spoke severe things , charging her with ingratitude and unkindness . 
And so indeed it was . 
The stranger , whose name was Antonio , was a sea captain . 
He had taken Sebastian up into his ship , when , almost exhausted with fatigue , he was floating on the mast to which he had fastened himself in the storm . 
This was the offence for which he was now made a prisoner . 
Antonio and Sebastian had landed together but a few hours before Antonio met Viola . 
disowned him , and denied him his own purse , no wonder he accused him of ingratitude . 
Viola , when Antonio was gone , fearing a second invitation to fight , slunk home as fast as she could . 
Sebastian was no coward he returned the blow with interest , and drew his sword . 
Sebastian did not at all object to the fondness the lady lavished on him . 
In the meantime Orsino came to visit Olivia and at the moment he arrived before Olivia's house , the officers of justice brought their prisoner , Antonio , before the duke . 
